# Plan: drop Signal Processing Toolbox dependency + annotate FFT peaks

## Context

The angular-acceleration FFT plot I added to `run_sysid.m` uses `hann(n)` (`run_sysid.m:376`) for windowing. `hann` lives in the Signal Processing Toolbox — users without that toolbox get a license error. The user also wants the FFT plot to **call out peak amplitudes** so the spectral hotspots are readable at a glance.

Confirmed by grep (recursive `\b(hann|hamming|blackman|kaiser|pwelch|cpsd|mscohere|tfestimate|findpeaks|filtfilt|freqz|spectrogram|xcorr|medfilt1|sgolay|bandpass|lowpass|highpass|butter|cheby1|cheby2|ellip|hilbert|envelope|window)\s*\(` over `/home/choudhury/tools/dev/sysID_matlab` and `/home/choudhury/repos/sysID_tool`): the **only** Signal Processing Toolbox call in the entire pipeline is that one `hann(n)`. Fixing it removes the toolbox requirement entirely.

Existing code already in `run_sysid.m::make_angular_accel_fft` (~lines 358-414):
