## Change 2: peak annotation on the FFT plot

Replace the existing per-axis subplot body (currently just `plot(f(mask), mag(mask, ax), ...)` + labels) with:

```matlab
fm = f(mask);
ym = mag(mask, ax);

plot(fm, ym, 'LineWidth', 1.0); grid on; hold on;

% Find peaks. islocalmax (base MATLAB, R2017b+) — no toolbox.
% MinSeparation in Hz, prominence ~10% of axis peak filters tiny ripples.
pk_mask = islocalmax(ym, 'MinSeparation', 1.5, 'SamplePoints', fm, ...
                         'MinProminence', 0.1*max(ym));
fp = fm(pk_mask); yp = ym(pk_mask);

% Keep top N by amplitude
N_show = 5;
if numel(fp) > N_show
    [~, ord] = sort(yp, 'descend');
    keep = ord(1:N_show);
    fp = fp(keep); yp = yp(keep);
end

if ~isempty(fp)
    plot(fp, yp, 'rv', 'MarkerSize', 8, 'MarkerFaceColor', 'r');
    for kk = 1:numel(fp)
        text(fp(kk), yp(kk), sprintf('  %.1f Hz\n  %.3f', fp(kk), yp(kk)), ...
             'VerticalAlignment','bottom', 'FontSize', 8, 'Color', 'r');
    end
end

ylabel(sprintf('|FFT(%s)| (rad/s^2)', axes_names{ax}));
% (title + xlabel lines kept as-is)
```

Why these choices:
- **`islocalmax`** is base MATLAB (R2017b+) — no toolbox.
- **`MinSeparation` 1.5 Hz** prevents the same physical peak from being annotated multiple times on adjacent FFT bins, which is what would happen at high `n` (frequency resolution = fs/n typically ≪ 1 Hz).
- **`MinProminence` 10% of `max(ym)`** rejects noise-floor wiggles. Computed per axis so an axis with low overall content still gets its real peaks flagged.
- **Top-5 cap** keeps the figure readable on dense spectra. Number is arbitrary; trivial to bump.
- Red downward triangles at peaks + text labels showing `"f Hz / amp"` directly on the plot — no separate legend or sidebar needed.

